                <head>112. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On May 7, representatives of the Governments of France and the United States
                    signed an agreement at Washington entitled “French-United States Cooperation in
                    the Uses of Atomic Energy.” It provided for the sale to the Government of France
                    of a specified quantity of enriched uranium for use in the development and
                    operation of a land-based prototype submarine nuclear propulsion plant during a
                    10-year period. For text of this agreement, see 10 UST 1279. Documentation on
                    the agreement is in Department of State, Central Files, 751.5621 /4–259.</p>
            </div>
